Pan-African Airline, Asky has announced the launch of its daily flights from Lagos to Johannesburg beginning from June 15, 2019. The airline said Johannesburg, South Africa would be connected to Lagos, Nigeria daily. According to an official statement from the airline, signed by Nowel Ngala, Commercial Director, Asky, the flights would be operated with a Boeing 737-800 NG aircraft. Asky currently operates a fleet of 8 new generation aircrafts, one  Boeing 737 – 800, five Boeing 737-700 and two  Dash Q-400, with service to 23 cities in 19 countries within Africa. According to the airline, its focus was to develop intra-Africa routes network in order to facilitate regional integration, economic and tourism development.